---
title: Prospect Mode & Training Hook Sequences
---
%% ==========================================
%% PURPOSE: Shows the control flow inverted where the Trainee acts as the Salesperson, mapping how the AI buyer scores readiness, combined with the quiz and training feedback hooks.
%% ==========================================
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "sequence": {"actorMargin": 30, "messageMargin": 25}}}%%

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    box rgba(102,187,106,0.15) Client
        participant Br  as Browser
    end
    box rgba(66,165,245,0.15) Web Layer
        participant App as app.py
    end
    box rgba(171,71,188,0.15) Feature Modules
        participant PS  as ProspectSession
        participant PE  as ProspectEvaluator
    end
    box rgba(255,167,38,0.15) Core Config
        participant Ldr as loader.py
    end
    box rgba(236,64,122,0.15) Provider Layer
        participant Pv  as Provider (Groq)
        participant API as Groq Cloud API
    end

    %% ── Session Start ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Br->>App: POST /api/prospect/start
    Note right of App: {product_type, difficulty, persona, session_id}
    App->>PS: ProspectSession(provider_type, product_type, difficulty, persona, session_id)
    PS->>Ldr: load_prospect_config()  [cached via @lru_cache]
    Ldr-->>PS: personas · difficulty_profiles · patience_turns · readiness_params

    Note over PS: ProspectState initialised:<br/>readiness = difficulty_profile.initial_readiness<br/>turn_count = 0<br/>has_committed = False<br/>has_walked = False<br/>Difficulty initial_readiness:<br/>easy → 0.4 (higher starting point, generous gain/loss)<br/>medium → 0.25 (balanced gain/loss)<br/>hard → 0.1 (low start, punishing loss, short patience)

    PS->>Pv: provider.chat([system_prompt + opening_message_request])
    Pv->>API: HTTPS llama-3.3-70b-versatile
    API-->>Pv: buyer opening line
    Pv-->>PS: LLMResponse
    PS-->>App: ProspectResponse {content, readiness, readiness_label, outcome=null, turn_count=0}
    App-->>Br: JSON {prospect_message, readiness, readiness_label, turn_count}  

    %% ── Per-Turn Loop ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    loop Each salesperson turn

        Br->>App: POST /api/prospect/chat  {user_message, show_hints, session_id}
        App->>PS: process_turn(user_message, show_hints)

        Note over PS: STEP 1 — Readiness Scoring  (DETERMINISTIC — zero LLM calls)<br/>_score_sales_message(user_msg, recent_bot_response) → score 1–5:<br/>+2 commitment signal (signals.yaml)     +1 high_intent signal<br/>+1 length bonus (long message)          +1 question bonus ('?' present)<br/>-2 walking signal (walkaway keywords)   -0.5 objection signal<br/>-1 impatience signal<br/>-1 early-turn penalty (premature price/feature mention)

        Note over PS: STEP 2 — Update Readiness<br/>score 4–5 → readiness += difficulty_gain   (e.g. easy: +0.15)<br/>score 1–2 → readiness -= difficulty_loss   (e.g. hard: -0.20)<br/>score 3   → readiness += 0.01  (negligible progress)<br/>clamp to [0.0, 1.0]

        Note over PS: STEP 3 — End Condition Check<br/>SOLD:   readiness >= 0.85  AND  turn_count >= 3<br/>WALKED: (turn_count >= patience_turns AND readiness < 0.4)<br/>OR readiness <= 0.0

        alt outcome == "sold"
            PS->>PS: state.has_committed = True
            PS-->>App: ProspectResponse {outcome: "sold", readiness, turn_count}
        else outcome == "walked"
            PS->>PS: state.has_walked = True
            PS-->>App: ProspectResponse {outcome: "walked", readiness, turn_count}
        else conversation continues
            PS->>Pv: provider.chat(system_prompt + conversation_history)        
            Pv->>API: HTTPS request  (buyer reply generation)
            API-->>Pv: buyer reply text
            Pv-->>PS: LLMResponse

            opt show_hints == True
                PS->>PS: _generate_coaching_hint(user_message)
                PS->>Pv: LLM call — generate hint for this turn
                Pv-->>PS: hint {title, suggestion, tip}
            end

            PS-->>App: ProspectResponse {content, readiness, readiness_label, hint, turn_count}
        end

        App-->>Br: JSON {prospect_message, readiness, readiness_label, outcome, hint}
    end

    %% ── Post-Session Evaluation ──────────────────────────────────────────────
    Br->>App: POST /api/prospect/evaluate  {session_id}
    App->>PS: get_evaluation()
    PS->>PE: evaluate_session(session_data, provider)

    Note over PE,Pv: LLM rubric scoring — 5 dimensions:<br/>NEPQ stage coverage · objection handling<br/>rapport building · close attempt · listening

    PE->>Pv: Send evaluation scoring request
    Pv->>API: HTTPS request
    API-->>Pv: scores + feedback text
    Pv-->>PE: structured evaluation dict
    PE-->>PS: {rubric_scores, overall_score, strengths, improvements}
    PS-->>App: evaluation dict
    App-->>Br: JSON {evaluation, session_summary}

    %% ── Training Feature (every /api/chat turn) ──────────────────────────────
    Note over App,Pv: TRAINING FEATURE — runs on EVERY /api/chat response (NOT prospect mode)<br/>app.py calls bot.generate_training(user_message, bot_reply) UNCONDITIONALLY<br/>trainer.generate_training(provider, flow_engine, user_msg, bot_reply):<br/>System prompt includes: current FSM stage · expected NEPQ technique<br/>what user said · what bot replied<br/>LLM returns: {stage_goal, what_bot_did, next_trigger, where_heading, watch_for: list[str]}<br/>Returned to browser in every /api/chat JSON response under 'training' key

    %% ── Quiz Feature ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    opt Trainee requests quiz
        Br->>App: GET /api/quiz/question?type={stage|next-move|direction}       
        App-->>Br: question text from quiz_config.yaml

        Br->>App: POST /api/quiz/stage  {answer}
        Note over App: Stage-ID quiz is DETERMINISTIC:<br/>compare answer to current FSM stage name — no LLM
        App-->>Br: {correct: bool, correct_answer: str, explanation: str}       

        Br->>App: POST /api/quiz/next-move  {response, last_user_message}       
        Note over App: Next-move quiz is LLM-scored:<br/>compare user's response to ideal next technique
        App->>Pv: LLM evaluation call
        Pv-->>App: score + feedback
        App-->>Br: {score: int, feedback: str, ideal_response: str}
    end
